<subSubSection id="38F506018562D4095C92A721E39BAC21" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="49720100437A1D2AB455CA2049143AF9" pageNumber="245">
One worker from Chiapas, soil. Agreeing very well with Mann's description and figure, except that the size is a little larger than Mann's measurements. Mann designated 
<taxonomicName id="E8A29BA35B51970DCF297C4C5CE5B1D6" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:24828" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Belonopelta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Belonopelta Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Belonopelta</taxonomicName>
as nominate subgenus to his 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="92766D56C7FE8259E2D1FB351A345BBE" rank="subGenus">new subgenus</taxonomicNameLabel>
<taxonomicName id="3AE83D75E3D81660D745AFCC033D2E1C" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:24850" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Simopelta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Simopelta Mann" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Simopelta</taxonomicName>
. Wheeler later separated the two generically by means of abundant characters. It does not seem to have been noticed that 
<taxonomicName id="89C8B7C03FE844CFB1B7FB714CD59D45" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:26053" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Belonopelta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Belonopelta deletrix Mann" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deletrix">B. deletrix</taxonomicName>
has minute lateral spurs beside the larger medial ones on the middle and posterior tibiae. Specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="682FE7663433B0125FFDE280524DF107" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:36093" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Simopelta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Simopelta jeckylli (Mann)" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jeckylli">Simopelta jeckylli Mann</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="0F28B8555078394A77B8B3B004480F42" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:36100" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Simopelta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Simopelta williamsi Wheeler" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="williamsi">Simopelta williamsi Wheeler</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C87BBE9B25C32D13E20894DF783699C" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:36095" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Simopelta" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Simopelta manni Wheeler" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="245" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manni">Simopelta manni Wheeler</taxonomicName>
all lack such lateral spurs completely, so this lack may afford an additional generic character.
</paragraph>
